The TDD cycle is complete. All 9 tests implemented and passing:

1. Empty grid returns empty array
2. Single live cell dies (underpopulation)
3. Two adjacent cells both die (underpopulation)
4. Cell with 2 live neighbors survives
5. Cell with 3 live neighbors survives
6. Cell with 4+ live neighbors dies (overpopulation)
7. Dead cell with exactly 3 neighbors becomes alive (reproduction)
8. 2x2 block stays unchanged (still life)
9. Blinker evolves from vertical to horizontal (oscillator)

The implementation uses a sparse representation with `Cell = [number, number]` coordinates, handles infinite grids and negative coordinates, and was refactored through each cycle to improve clarity and reduce duplication.
